INSERT INTO contract_templates (contract_type, jurisdiction, version, title, preamble, recitals, clauses, signature_block, placeholders, is_active, metadata) VALUES (
  'safe_note',
  'uk',
  2,
  'Advance Subscription Agreement (United Kingdom)',
  'This Advance Subscription Agreement (this "Agreement") is entered into and effective as of {{effective_date}} (the "Effective Date") by and between {{party_a_company}}, a company registered in England and Wales with company number {{company_number}} and registered office at {{party_a_address}} (the "Company"), and {{party_b_name}}, with address at {{party_b_address}} (the "Investor").',
  'WHEREAS, the Company is seeking to raise capital to fund its business operations and growth;

WHEREAS, the Investor wishes to invest in the Company by way of an advance subscription for shares on the terms set forth herein;

WHEREAS, the parties intend that this Agreement complies with and benefits from applicable exemptions under the Financial Services and Markets Act 2000 ("FSMA") and the Financial Services and Markets Act 2000 (Financial Promotion) Order 2005 (the "FPO"), and that no prospectus is required to be published under the UK Prospectus Regulation (as retained and amended in UK law);

WHEREAS, this Agreement is based on principles similar to the Y Combinator Simple Agreement for Future Equity (SAFE) adapted for UK company law and regulatory requirements;

WHEREAS, the parties intend that this Agreement constitutes a legally binding agreement under the laws of England and Wales.

NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual covenants contained herein, the parties agree as follows:',
  '[{"id":"definitions","title":"1. DEFINITIONS AND INTERPRETATION","content":"1.1 \"Advance Subscription Amount\" means {{investment_amount}}, being the amount paid by the Investor to the Company under this Agreement.\n\n1.2 \"Conversion Event\" means the first to occur of: (a) a Qualifying Funding Round; (b) a Sale; or (c) the Long Stop Date.\n\n1.3 \"Qualifying Funding Round\" means the first equity funding round (whether by way of subscription for or allotment of shares) in which the Company raises at least {{qualifying_round_threshold}} in aggregate (excluding any amounts subscribed under this Agreement and any other advance subscription agreements or convertible loan notes).\n\n1.4 \"Discount Rate\" means {{discount_rate}}%, being the discount applied to the share price in a Qualifying Funding Round.\n\n1.5 \"Valuation Cap\" means {{valuation_cap}}, being the maximum pre-money valuation of the Company used to calculate the conversion price.\n\n1.6 \"Sale\" means: (a) a sale of all or substantially all of the Company''s business, assets, or undertaking; (b) a sale, transfer, or disposal (whether by a single transaction or series of related transactions) of shares representing more than 50% of the voting rights of the Company; (c) a merger, consolidation, scheme of arrangement, or similar transaction in which the Company''s shareholders immediately prior to such transaction hold less than 50% of the voting rights of the surviving or combined entity; or (d) an initial public offering or admission of the Company''s shares to trading on a recognised stock exchange.\n\n1.7 \"Long Stop Date\" means {{long_stop_date}}, being the date by which conversion must occur if no other Conversion Event has occurred.\n\n1.8 \"Conversion Shares\" means the ordinary shares (or shares of the class issued in a Qualifying Funding Round, as applicable) to be allotted and issued to the Investor upon conversion.\n\n1.9 \"Companies Act\" means the Companies Act 2006, as amended from time to time.\n\n1.10 \"FSMA\" means the Financial Services and Markets Act 2000, as amended from time to time.\n\n1.11 \"FPO\" means the Financial Services and Markets Act 2000 (Financial Promotion) Order 2005, as amended from time to time.\n\n1.12 \"FCA\" means the Financial Conduct Authority.\n\n1.13 \"UK GDPR\" means the General Data Protection Regulation (EU) 2016/679 as it forms part of retained EU law in the United Kingdom, together with the Data Protection Act 2018.\n\n1.14 \"Fully-Diluted Share Capital\" means the total number of issued shares of the Company, calculated on a fully-diluted basis as if all outstanding options, warrants, convertible instruments (including this Agreement), and other rights to acquire shares had been exercised or converted in full.","type":"standard","order":1},{"id":"advance_subscription","title":"2. ADVANCE SUBSCRIPTION","content":"2.1 Subscription. Subject to the terms of this Agreement, the Investor agrees to subscribe for, and the Company agrees to allot and issue, Conversion Shares upon the occurrence of a Conversion Event in accordance with the terms of this Agreement.\n\n2.2 Payment. Within five (5) business days of the Effective Date (or such other date as the parties may agree), the Investor shall pay the Advance Subscription Amount to the Company by bank transfer to the following account (or such other account as the Company may notify in writing):\nBank: {{bank_name}}\nAccount Name: {{account_name}}\nSort Code: {{sort_code}}\nAccount Number: {{account_number}}\n\n2.3 No Interest. The Advance Subscription Amount does not bear interest.\n\n2.4 Application of Funds. The Company shall apply the Advance Subscription Amount for general working capital, business operations, and such other purposes as the Company''s directors may determine in their reasonable discretion.\n\n2.5 Not a Loan. This Agreement does not create a loan or debt obligation. The Advance Subscription Amount is not repayable except as expressly provided in this Agreement. The Investor''s rights are limited to receiving Conversion Shares upon a Conversion Event or the other remedies expressly set forth herein.\n\n2.6 Receipt Acknowledgment. The Company acknowledges receipt of the Advance Subscription Amount upon clearance of funds into the designated account.","type":"standard","order":2},{"id":"conversion","title":"3. CONVERSION MECHANICS","content":"3.1 Conversion on Qualifying Funding Round. Upon the completion of a Qualifying Funding Round, the Advance Subscription Amount shall automatically convert into Conversion Shares at a price per share (the \"Conversion Price\") equal to the lower of:\n\n(a) the price per share paid by investors in the Qualifying Funding Round multiplied by (100% minus the Discount Rate); or\n\n(b) the Valuation Cap divided by the Fully-Diluted Share Capital immediately prior to the Qualifying Funding Round (calculated on a pre-money basis, excluding the shares to be issued in the Qualifying Funding Round).\n\n3.2 Conversion on Sale. If a Sale occurs before a Qualifying Funding Round, the Investor may elect (by written notice to the Company not less than five (5) business days prior to completion of the Sale) to:\n\n(a) receive a cash payment from the proceeds of the Sale equal to two times (2x) the Advance Subscription Amount (the \"Liquidation Multiple\"), subject to available proceeds after payment of all secured and unsecured creditors and any preferential shareholders; or\n\n(b) convert the Advance Subscription Amount into Conversion Shares immediately prior to completion of the Sale at a price per share equal to the Valuation Cap divided by the Fully-Diluted Share Capital, and participate in the Sale on the same terms as other ordinary shareholders.\n\nIf the Investor fails to make an election, the Investor shall be deemed to have elected option (a).\n\n3.3 Conversion on Long Stop Date. If no other Conversion Event occurs by the Long Stop Date, the Advance Subscription Amount shall automatically convert into Conversion Shares at a price per share equal to the Valuation Cap divided by the Fully-Diluted Share Capital as at the Long Stop Date.\n\n3.4 Anti-Dilution Adjustment. The Conversion Price shall be subject to proportional adjustment for share splits, share consolidations, bonus issues, and similar corporate actions affecting the Company''s share capital.\n\n3.5 Mechanics of Conversion. Upon conversion:\n(a) the Company shall allot and issue the Conversion Shares to the Investor credited as fully paid;\n(b) the Investor shall be entered in the Company''s register of members as the holder of the Conversion Shares;\n(c) share certificates (or a statement of uncertificated holdings) shall be issued to the Investor within ten (10) business days of conversion;\n(d) the Company shall update its statutory registers and file all necessary returns with Companies House.\n\n3.6 Fractional Shares. No fractional shares shall be issued. Any fractional entitlement shall be rounded down to the nearest whole share, with no cash payment for the fractional portion unless agreed otherwise.","type":"negotiable","order":3},{"id":"distribution_waterfall","title":"4. DISTRIBUTION WATERFALL AND PRIORITY","content":"4.1 Priority on Sale or Liquidation. In the event of a Sale or a winding up or liquidation of the Company (other than for the purposes of a solvent reorganisation) prior to conversion, the Company''s assets available for distribution shall be applied in the following order of priority:\n\n(a) First, to creditors (including employees) in accordance with applicable law and the statutory order of priority under the Insolvency Act 1986;\n(b) Second, to holders of shares with preferential rights to capital, in accordance with the Company''s articles of association;\n(c) Third, to holders of advance subscription agreements (including this Agreement) and convertible loan notes on a pari passu basis, pro rata based on their respective subscription amounts, up to the Liquidation Multiple;\n(d) Finally, to holders of ordinary shares.\n\n4.2 Insufficient Proceeds. If the proceeds available for distribution to advance subscription holders and convertible loan note holders are insufficient to pay all such holders in full at the Liquidation Multiple, such holders shall share pro rata in the available proceeds based on their respective subscription amounts.","type":"standard","order":4},{"id":"valuation_discount","title":"5. VALUATION CAP AND DISCOUNT MECHANICS","content":"5.1 Valuation Cap. The Valuation Cap for purposes of this Agreement is {{valuation_cap}}. The Valuation Cap represents the maximum effective pre-money valuation at which this Agreement will convert, providing the Investor with downside protection if the Company achieves a higher valuation in a subsequent Qualifying Funding Round.\n\n5.2 Discount Rate. The Discount Rate for purposes of this Agreement is {{discount_rate}}%. The Discount provides the Investor with a reduction from the price per share paid by investors in the Qualifying Funding Round, in recognition of the Investor''s early-stage investment risk.\n\n5.3 Better of Cap or Discount. In calculating the Conversion Price, the Investor will receive whichever of the Cap-based price or Discount-based price results in more shares (i.e., the lower price per share), not both.\n\n5.4 Example Calculation. [For illustration only] If the Valuation Cap is GBP 5,000,000, the Fully-Diluted Share Capital is 10,000,000 shares, the Discount Rate is 20%, and the Qualifying Funding Round price is GBP 1.00 per share: Cap Price = GBP 5,000,000 / 10,000,000 = GBP 0.50; Discount Price = GBP 1.00 x (1 - 0.20) = GBP 0.80; Conversion Price = GBP 0.50 (lower of the two).","type":"negotiable","order":5},{"id":"mfn_provision","title":"6. MOST FAVOURED NATION (MFN) PROVISION","content":"6.1 MFN Right. If, prior to the conversion or termination of this Agreement, the Company issues any subsequent advance subscription agreement, convertible loan note, or similar convertible instrument (a \"Subsequent Convertible\") on terms more favourable to the investor thereunder than the terms of this Agreement, including without limitation: (a) a higher Valuation Cap (which would be more favourable to the Investor); (b) a higher Discount Rate; (c) a higher Liquidation Multiple; (d) more favourable conversion mechanics; or (e) additional investor rights not provided herein, then the Investor shall have the right, upon written notice to the Company within thirty (30) days after receiving notice of such issuance, to amend this Agreement to incorporate such more favourable terms.\n\n6.2 Notice Requirement. The Company shall provide the Investor with written notice of any Subsequent Convertible issuance within ten (10) business days of such issuance, including a summary of the material terms thereof.\n\n6.3 Amendment Mechanics. If the Investor elects to exercise MFN rights, the parties shall execute a deed of variation to this Agreement incorporating the more favourable terms, effective as of the date of issuance of the Subsequent Convertible.\n\n6.4 Exceptions. The MFN right shall not apply to: (a) issuances to employees, directors, or consultants under share option schemes or share incentive plans approved by the Company''s board of directors; (b) issuances in connection with strategic transactions approved by the Company''s board of directors; or (c) amendments to existing convertible instruments that do not involve new subscription monies.","type":"negotiable","order":6},{"id":"pro_rata_rights","title":"7. PRO RATA RIGHTS","content":"7.1 Grant of Pro Rata Right. Subject to the limitations in this Section 7, the Company grants the Investor a pre-emption right to subscribe for additional shares (at the same price and on substantially the same terms as offered to other investors) in a Qualifying Funding Round, in order to maintain the Investor''s percentage shareholding in the Company on a fully-diluted basis immediately following conversion of this Agreement (the \"Pro Rata Right\").\n\n7.2 Calculation. The Investor''s pro rata entitlement shall be calculated in good faith by the Company based on the Fully-Diluted Share Capital immediately prior to the closing of the Qualifying Funding Round, taking into account the conversion of this Agreement.\n\n7.3 Notice and Election. The Company shall provide the Investor with written notice (email to {{party_b_email}} is sufficient) describing the Qualifying Funding Round, the Investor''s pro rata allocation, and the deadline to elect participation. The election deadline shall be not less than {{notice_period}} days after the notice is sent.\n\n7.4 Limitations and Exclusions. The Pro Rata Right does not apply to: (a) issuances under employee share option schemes or share incentive plans; (b) securities issued in connection with equipment financings or debt facilities; (c) securities issued as consideration in acquisitions or strategic transactions; (d) securities issued upon conversion of convertible instruments; or (e) other excluded issuances approved by the Company''s board of directors.\n\n7.5 Statutory Pre-emption Rights. The Pro Rata Right under this Agreement is in addition to, and does not limit or exclude, any statutory pre-emption rights the Investor may have under Section 561 of the Companies Act (to the extent not disapplied by the Company''s articles of association or shareholder resolutions).","type":"optional","order":7},{"id":"information_rights","title":"8. INFORMATION RIGHTS","content":"8.1 Basic Information Rights. Until the earlier of (a) the conversion of this Agreement into Conversion Shares, or (b) the termination of this Agreement, the Company shall provide the Investor with:\n\n(a) Annual unaudited financial statements (profit and loss account and balance sheet) within one hundred twenty (120) days after each financial year end;\n\n(b) Notification of any proposed Qualifying Funding Round, Sale, or other Conversion Event at least ten (10) business days before completion (or such shorter period as may be commercially necessary);\n\n(c) Upon reasonable request, access to information reasonably necessary for the Investor to comply with tax reporting requirements.\n\n8.2 Confidentiality. The Investor agrees to keep confidential all non-public information received from the Company pursuant to this Section 8 and to use such information solely for the purpose of monitoring the Investor''s investment in the Company, subject to disclosure: (a) to the Investor''s professional advisers bound by confidentiality; (b) as required by law, regulation, or court order; (c) to potential investors or acquirers under appropriate confidentiality undertakings; or (d) with the Company''s prior written consent.\n\n8.3 Termination of Information Rights. Upon conversion of this Agreement into Conversion Shares, the information rights under this Section 8 shall terminate, and the Investor''s information rights (if any) shall be governed by the Company''s articles of association and any shareholders'' agreement.","type":"standard","order":8},{"id":"company_warranties","title":"9. COMPANY REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES","content":"The Company represents and warrants to the Investor as at the Effective Date that:\n\n9.1 Incorporation and Standing. The Company is a private company limited by shares, duly incorporated and validly existing under the laws of England and Wales, and registered with Companies House with company number {{company_number}}.\n\n9.2 Authority and Capacity. The Company has full power and authority to enter into, execute, and perform this Agreement. The execution and performance of this Agreement have been duly authorised by all necessary corporate action, including any required board resolutions.\n\n9.3 Binding Obligation. This Agreement constitutes a valid and binding obligation of the Company, enforceable against the Company in accordance with its terms, subject to: (a) applicable bankruptcy, insolvency, reorganisation, or similar laws affecting creditors'' rights generally; and (b) general principles of equity.\n\n9.4 No Conflict. The execution and performance of this Agreement do not and will not: (a) breach the Company''s articles of association or any shareholders'' agreement; (b) breach any material contract or agreement to which the Company is a party; or (c) violate any applicable law or regulation.\n\n9.5 Allotment of Shares. Upon conversion, the Company shall have sufficient authorised but unissued share capital to allot and issue the Conversion Shares, or shall procure the necessary shareholder approvals to increase its share capital.\n\n9.6 No Insolvency. No order has been made, petition presented, or resolution passed for the winding up of the Company; no administrator, receiver, or administrative receiver has been appointed over the Company or any of its assets; and the Company is not insolvent or unable to pay its debts as they fall due.\n\n9.7 Regulatory Compliance. The offer and issue of this Agreement and the Conversion Shares does not require a prospectus to be published under the UK Prospectus Regulation, and is being made in reliance on applicable exemptions under FSMA and the FPO. The Company has not applied for authorisation under FSMA and is not required to be authorised to enter into this Agreement.\n\n9.8 No Broker. The Company has not engaged any broker, finder, or financial adviser entitled to any fee or commission payable by the Investor in connection with this Agreement.","type":"standard","order":9},{"id":"investor_warranties","title":"10. INVESTOR REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES","content":"The Investor represents and warrants to the Company as at the Effective Date that:\n\n10.1 Authority and Capacity. The Investor has full power, authority, and legal capacity to enter into, execute, and perform this Agreement.\n\n10.2 Binding Obligation. This Agreement constitutes a valid and binding obligation of the Investor, enforceable against the Investor in accordance with its terms.\n\n10.3 Sophisticated Investor Status. The Investor falls within one or more of the following categories under the FPO:\n(a) A \"high net worth individual\" within the meaning of Article 48 of the FPO (i.e., an individual who has signed, within the preceding twelve months, a statement that they had during the preceding financial year an annual income of not less than GBP 100,000 or net assets (excluding primary residence, pension rights, and certain insurance contracts) of not less than GBP 250,000); or\n(b) A \"self-certified sophisticated investor\" within the meaning of Article 50A of the FPO (i.e., an individual who has signed, within the preceding twelve months, a statement that they are a member of a network or syndicate of business angels, have made more than one investment in an unlisted company in the previous two years, are working or have worked in the previous two years in a professional capacity in the private equity sector or in the provision of finance for small and medium enterprises, or are currently or have been in the previous two years a director of a company with an annual turnover of at least GBP 1,000,000); or\n(c) A \"certified sophisticated investor\" within the meaning of Article 50 of the FPO; or\n(d) A \"professional client\" or \"eligible counterparty\" within the meaning of the FCA Handbook.\n\n10.4 Investment Purpose. The Investor is acquiring this Agreement and any Conversion Shares for their own account for investment purposes and not with a view to distribution or resale.\n\n10.5 Risk Acknowledgment. The Investor acknowledges and understands that:\n(a) Investment in early-stage companies involves a high degree of risk, including the risk of total loss of the entire investment;\n(b) The Company may not succeed and the Investor may receive no return on this investment;\n(c) Shares in private companies are illiquid and there may be no market for the Conversion Shares;\n(d) Past performance is not indicative of future results;\n(e) The Investor has had the opportunity to ask questions of and receive answers from the Company.\n\n10.6 No Advice. The Investor is not relying on any tax, legal, or investment advice from the Company or its advisers. The Investor has obtained or has had the opportunity to obtain independent professional advice.\n\n10.7 Residence. The Investor''s address set forth in this Agreement is the Investor''s principal residence (if an individual) or principal place of business (if an entity).\n\n10.8 Anti-Money Laundering. The Investor is not subject to any sanctions administered by OFAC, HM Treasury, or any other governmental authority, and the funds used to make the investment do not derive from criminal activity.","type":"standard","order":10},{"id":"tax_matters","title":"11. TAX MATTERS","content":"11.1 EIS/SEIS Intention. The parties acknowledge that the Investor may intend to claim tax relief under the Enterprise Investment Scheme (\"EIS\") or Seed Enterprise Investment Scheme (\"SEIS\") in respect of the Conversion Shares (subject to eligibility). The Company shall:\n\n(a) use reasonable endeavours (without being obliged to change its business activities or operations) to ensure that the Conversion Shares, when issued, qualify as eligible shares for EIS or SEIS relief, where the Investor is eligible to claim such relief;\n\n(b) upon request by the Investor (and where the Company reasonably believes EIS or SEIS relief may be available), apply to HMRC for advance assurance that EIS or SEIS relief will be available;\n\n(c) provide the Investor with completed EIS3 or SEIS3 compliance certificates and any other information reasonably required by the Investor to claim EIS or SEIS relief, within a reasonable time after the Conversion Shares are issued;\n\n(d) notify the Investor promptly if the Company becomes aware of any circumstances that may affect the availability of EIS or SEIS relief.\n\n11.2 No Guarantee of Tax Relief. The Company does not guarantee that EIS or SEIS relief will be available to the Investor. The availability of such relief depends on the individual circumstances of the Investor and the Company and is subject to HMRC approval. The Investor acknowledges that tax treatment may change and that they should seek independent tax advice.\n\n11.3 Investor''s Tax Responsibility. The Investor is solely responsible for their own tax position, including any stamp duty, stamp duty reserve tax, income tax, capital gains tax, or other taxes arising in connection with this Agreement or the Conversion Shares. The Investor should seek independent professional tax advice.\n\n11.4 Withholding. The Company shall be entitled to deduct and withhold from any payments under this Agreement any amounts required to be deducted or withheld under applicable tax laws.","type":"optional","order":11},{"id":"data_protection","title":"12. DATA PROTECTION","content":"12.1 Data Processing. In connection with this Agreement, the Company will process personal data relating to the Investor (including name, address, email, identification documents, and financial information). The Company processes this personal data as a data controller for the purposes of:\n(a) administering the investment relationship and performing its obligations under this Agreement;\n(b) maintaining the Company''s statutory registers and making filings with Companies House;\n(c) complying with anti-money laundering, know-your-customer, and tax reporting obligations;\n(d) communicating with the Investor regarding the Company and future funding rounds.\n\n12.2 Legal Basis. The Company processes the Investor''s personal data on the basis of: (a) performance of this Agreement; (b) compliance with legal obligations; and (c) the Company''s legitimate interests in managing its shareholders and investors.\n\n12.3 Data Retention. The Company will retain the Investor''s personal data for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes set out above, and in any event for at least six (6) years after termination of the investment relationship (or longer if required by law).\n\n12.4 Data Sharing. The Company may share the Investor''s personal data with: (a) its professional advisers (lawyers, accountants, auditors) under appropriate confidentiality obligations; (b) Companies House and HMRC as required by law; (c) potential acquirers or investors in connection with a Sale or financing (subject to confidentiality); and (d) other third parties where required by law or with the Investor''s consent.\n\n12.5 Investor Rights. Under UK GDPR, the Investor has rights to access, rectification, erasure, restriction of processing, data portability, and objection. To exercise these rights, the Investor may contact the Company at the address set forth in this Agreement.\n\n12.6 The Company''s privacy policy is available at {{privacy_policy_url}} (or upon request).","type":"standard","order":12},{"id":"transfer_assignment","title":"13. TRANSFER AND ASSIGNMENT","content":"13.1 Company Assignment. The Company may not assign its rights or obligations under this Agreement without the Investor''s prior written consent, except that the Company may assign this Agreement without consent to a successor entity in connection with a reorganisation, amalgamation, or Sale, provided the successor assumes all obligations under this Agreement.\n\n13.2 Investor Transfer. The Investor may not transfer or assign this Agreement without the Company''s prior written consent; provided, however, that the Investor may transfer this Agreement without consent to:\n(a) an affiliate of the Investor;\n(b) a trust for the benefit of the Investor or the Investor''s immediate family;\n(c) in the case of an individual, to the Investor''s spouse, civil partner, children, or lineal descendants;\n(d) in the case of an entity, to a successor in connection with a reorganisation;\n\nin each case, subject to the transferee agreeing in writing to be bound by this Agreement and compliance with applicable law.\n\n13.3 Legal Compliance. Any transfer must comply with applicable law, including securities laws and anti-money laundering requirements. The Company may require evidence of compliance as a condition to any transfer.","type":"negotiable","order":13},{"id":"termination","title":"14. TERMINATION","content":"14.1 Automatic Termination. This Agreement shall terminate automatically upon:\n(a) conversion of the full Advance Subscription Amount into Conversion Shares; or\n(b) payment to the Investor of amounts due upon a Sale (under Section 3.2(a)).\n\n14.2 Termination by Agreement. This Agreement may be terminated by mutual written agreement of the parties.\n\n14.3 Termination for Material Breach. Either party may terminate this Agreement by written notice if the other party commits a material breach of this Agreement and fails to remedy such breach within thirty (30) days of receiving written notice requiring it to do so.\n\n14.4 Effect of Termination. Upon termination (other than by conversion), the Advance Subscription Amount shall be returned to the Investor within thirty (30) days, unless this Agreement has already been converted or the Company is unable to make such payment due to insolvency. Termination shall not affect any accrued rights or remedies.\n\n14.5 Survival. Sections 8.2 (Confidentiality), 11 (Tax Matters), 12 (Data Protection), and 15 (Miscellaneous) shall survive termination of this Agreement.","type":"standard","order":14},{"id":"miscellaneous","title":"15. MISCELLANEOUS","content":"15.1 Governing Law. This Agreement and any dispute or claim arising out of or in connection with it shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the law of England and Wales.\n\n15.2 Jurisdiction. The courts of England and Wales shall have exclusive jurisdiction to settle any dispute or claim arising out of or in connection with this Agreement.\n\n15.3 Notices. Any notice under this Agreement shall be in writing and shall be deemed to have been duly given if: (a) delivered by hand (deemed delivered on delivery); (b) sent by first-class post (deemed delivered two (2) business days after posting); or (c) sent by email (deemed delivered on transmission, provided no delivery failure notice is received), to the addresses set forth in this Agreement or such other address as a party may notify in writing.\n\n15.4 Entire Agreement. This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties in relation to its subject matter and supersedes all prior agreements, understandings, and representations.\n\n15.5 Amendments. No amendment to this Agreement shall be effective unless in writing and signed by both parties (or executed as a deed of variation if required).\n\n15.6 Severability. If any provision of this Agreement is held to be invalid, illegal, or unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall continue in full force and effect, and the invalid provision shall be modified to the minimum extent necessary to make it valid and enforceable.\n\n15.7 Waiver. No waiver of any right or remedy under this Agreement shall be effective unless in writing. A waiver shall not be deemed a waiver of any subsequent breach or default.\n\n15.8 No Partnership. Nothing in this Agreement shall create a partnership, joint venture, or agency relationship between the parties.\n\n15.9 Third Party Rights. Except as expressly provided, no person who is not a party to this Agreement shall have any rights under the Contracts (Rights of Third Parties) Act 1999 to enforce any term of this Agreement.\n\n15.10 Counterparts. This Agreement may be executed in any number of counterparts, each of which shall constitute an original, and all of which together shall constitute one and the same agreement. Electronic signatures (including DocuSign or similar services) shall be valid and binding.\n\n15.11 Further Assurance. Each party shall, at its own cost, do all things and execute all documents as may be reasonably necessary to give effect to this Agreement.\n\n15.12 Costs. Each party shall bear its own costs and expenses incurred in connection with the negotiation, preparation, and execution of this Agreement.","type":"standard","order":15}]'::jsonb,
  'IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the parties have executed this Advance Subscription Agreement as of the Effective Date.

